page.title: 02WYE DOWNS
page.content: On Wye Downs all the flowers grow wild.They are mostly poppies.But when the bombs fell and ruined the wheat the poppies came up.So thats why we buy poppies for rememberance day.The orchid is purple and the roots has two small roots with thin and long roots coming out.Daisy were scattered over the Wye downs.Their petals are white and small.We found some vetch we thought it was Horse-shoe vetch, which is yellow and has separate petals. Wye Downs are a conservation area and no one is allowed to pick flowers there. the Downs are quite high and you can see them from all over our area.
